article_title: Obamacare Penalty May Not Be High Enough For Middle Incomes

article_metadata.author: Bruce Japsen

og.description: Even though penalties under the Affordable Care Act for not having health insurance jumped significantly this year, they still might be too low to attract Americans to signup for subsidized coverage, a new analysis shows.
